{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-wp-post-tsx","path":"/flatpak-linux","result":{"pageContext":{"id":"6723b53c-9c12-5db8-b84e-71db4c45df2c","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/behrouze/Sources/blog/obsidian/Blog/flatpak-linux.md","frontmatter":{"categories":["linux"],"date":"2018-09-24","lastUpdate":null,"tags":["apt","chocolatey","devops","docker","linux","package-manager"],"title":"Flatpak"},"html":"Flatpak est le <a href=\"/chocolatey\" title=\"chocolatey\">chocolatey</a> de Linux (disponible sur 16 distros) qui donne accès à une belle interface, simple et efficace pour installer simplement des applications sous Linux.\n<h1>Avantages</h1>\n<p>Les principaux points forts de cette solution sont:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>les applications distribuées à travers ce système sont <a href=\"http://docs.flatpak.org/en/latest/basic-concepts.html\">Sandboxées ou Containerisées</a>, ce qui <strong>évite de polluer son OS</strong> à dispatcher des fichiers à chaque installation ?</li>\n<li>le site <a href=\"https://flathub.org/home\">Flathub</a> <strong>centralise</strong> tout les outils avec un système de classification et notation des applis</li>\n<li>Flatpak s'<strong>intègre parfaitement à la GUI du package manager</strong> (j'ai testé avec <a href=\"https://userbase.kde.org/Discover\">Discover</a> de <a href=\"https://doc.ubuntu-fr.org/kde\">KDE</a>/<a href=\"https://www.kde.org/plasma-desktop\">Plasma</a>):</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 850px; box-shadow: 3px 5px 4px rgba(0,0,0,.1);margin:1rem;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 85.91549295774648%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/e10402676bfd37e41d29ad9138048d73/bc663/Screenshot_Discover_KDE_Flatpak.webp 213w,\n/static/e10402676bfd37e41d29ad9138048d73/8dc4f/Screenshot_Discover_KDE_Flatpak.webp 425w,\n/static/e10402676bfd37e41d29ad9138048d73/10237/Screenshot_Discover_KDE_Flatpak.webp 850w,\n/static/e10402676bfd37e41d29ad9138048d73/1b8e7/Screenshot_Discover_KDE_Flatpak.webp 1248w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/e10402676bfd37e41d29ad9138048d73/3cb16/Screenshot_Discover_KDE_Flatpak.png 213w,\n/static/e10402676bfd37e41d29ad9138048d73/2fbbf/Screenshot_Discover_KDE_Flatpak.png 425w,\n/static/e10402676bfd37e41d29ad9138048d73/ae694/Screenshot_Discover_KDE_Flatpak.png 850w,\n/static/e10402676bfd37e41d29ad9138048d73/5a791/Screenshot_Discover_KDE_Flatpak.png 1248w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/e10402676bfd37e41d29ad9138048d73/ae694/Screenshot_Discover_KDE_Flatpak.png\"\n            alt=\"KDE Flatpak\"\n            title=\"KDE Flatpak\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span></p>\n<h1>Installation</h1>\n<p>Sur les distributions Debian like (<a href=\"https://flatpak.org/setup/\">pour les autres</a>):</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">apt</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> flatpak\nflatpak remote-add --if-not-exists flathub https://flathub.org/repo/flathub.flatpakrepo\n<span class=\"token function\">sudo</span> <span class=\"token function\">reboot</span></code></pre></div>\n<h1>Astuces</h1>\n<p>Les outils installés via <strong>faltpak sont \"conteneurisés\"</strong>, les binaires ne sont donc <strong>pas directement accessibles depuis le PATH</strong> dans un shell. Cependant flatpak nous mets à disposition un lien vers chacune des application dans /var/lib/flatpak/exports/bin  qui pointe vers /var/lib/flatpak/app/ (en version 0.11.7 du moins) ce qui nous permet de créer notre <strong>alias</strong> qui va bien pour lancer par exemple VSCode avec la commande code  :</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">alias</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">code</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'/var/lib/flatpak/exports/bin/com.visualstudio.code'</span></code></pre></div>\n<h1>Liens</h1>\n<p>Article exposant les <a href=\"https://www.devpy.me/snapcraft-appimage-flatpak/\">différences entre Flatpak, SnapCraft et AppImage</a> et <a href=\"https://www.datamation.com/open-source/linux-solutions-snappy-flatpak-and-appimage.html\">un autre article</a><a href=\"https://www.devpy.me/snapcraft-appimage-flatpak/\"></a></p>"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1026020893","28434099","3153813225"]}